dc_title_s: Route map from Jask to Bampūr to accompany the paper by Mr. E. A. Floyer
dc_description_s: Relief shown by hachures and spot heights. Author's route, places not personally visited [by author], and routes from carefully accepted Native information are shown. Abundance of water, fodder, and firewood shown by text. Soil quality and vegetation shown by text and graphically. From: The Journal of the Royal Geographical Society of London. Vol. 47, (1877), pp. 188-201; held in Firestone Library. Call number: G7 .J687 v.47 1877
dc_publisher_s: London: published for the Journal of the Royal Geographical Society, by J. Murray, Albemarle Street, 1877.
